from Madeira as 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trochosa maderiana" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maderiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Trochosa maderiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T" journalOrPublisher="Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 204" refId="B71" refString="Thorell, T, 1875. Descriptions of several European and North African spiders. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar 13: 1 - 204" title="Descriptions of several European and North African spiders." volume="13" year="1875">Thorell 1875</bibRefCitation>
). We argue that the presence of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. maderiana" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maderiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">H. maderiana</emphasis>
